title: Prep roundup: Fossil Ridge volleyball wins 4th in a row
text:
Prep roundup: Fossil Ridge volleyball wins 4th in a row Coloradoan staff 9:13 p.m. MDT September 30, 2015 The Fossil Ridge volleyball team, shown in a game earlier this season, moved to 8-3 with a road win at Monarch on Wednesday. (Photo: Austin Humphreys/The Coloradoan) CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The Fossil Ridge High School volleyball team recorded its fourth win in a row with a sweep of Monarch on the road Wednesday night. 
The SaberCats won 25-19, 25-15, 25-19 to move to 8-3 and 4-0 in Front Range League play. Mataya Megson had 12 kills for Fossil Ridge and Riley Zuhn had nine. Reagan Warner had five aces and Zuhn and Brynn Montgomery had four blocks each.
